18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
20 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
21 This act shall be known and may be cited as "Rain's Law".
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.229-8 of Title 70, unless
24 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1484 Page 1

1 A. As part of the comprehensive, integrated curriculum for
2 substance abuse programs provided in Section 1210.229-5 of Title 70
3 of the Oklahoma Statutes, each school district shall annually
4 provide research-based instruction related to fentanyl abuse
5 prevention and drug poisoning awareness to students in grades six
6 through twelve.
7 B. The instruction required by this section shall include:
8 1. Suicide prevention;
9 2. Prevention of the abuse of and addiction to fentanyl;
10 3. Awareness of local school and community resources and how to
11 access those resources; and
12 4. Health education that includes information about substance
13 use and abuse of fentanyl, including youth substance use and abuse
14 of fentanyl.
15 C. The instruction required by this section may be provided by
16 an organization or an employee or agent of an organization that is:
17 1. A public or private institution of higher education;
18 2. A library;
19 3. A community service organization;
20 4. A religious organization;
21 5. A local public health agency; or
22 6. An organization employing mental health professionals.
23 D. The State Department of Education shall identify and adopt
24 curriculum standards for fentanyl awareness instruction that reflect
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1484 Page 2

1 the areas of instruction listed in subsection B of this section.
2 The standards shall be incorporated into the appropriate health
3 standards for grades six through twelve.
4 E. The State Department of Education shall provide resources to
5 assist schools and teachers in providing instruction on fentanyl
6 awareness.
7 F. Any school district that offers a health education class in
8 grades six through twelve shall include fentanyl awareness
9 curriculum in the drug awareness unit.
10 G. To educate students about the dangers posed by fentanyl and
11 the risks of fentanyl poisoning, including overdose, the Governor
12 shall designate a week to be known as Fentanyl Poisoning Awareness
13 Week in public schools. Fentanyl Poisoning Awareness Week shall be
14 in correlation with National Red Ribbon Week. Fentanyl Poisoning
15 Awareness Week may include age-appropriate instruction, including
16 instruction on the prevention of the abuse of and addiction to
17 fentanyl, as determined by each school district.
18 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
19 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
20 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
21 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
22 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
